# Database API conventions

- Every `app/api/db/*` handler must call `guardDbRoute(request)` first.
- Require `specId` and validate with `validateSpecId()` from `lib/spec-id`.
- Scope connections with `postgresDbConnectionRepository.findForSpec(specId, connectionId)` — never trust `connectionId` alone.
- User SQL must go through `sanitizeReadOnlySql` or `executeAgentReadOnlyQuery`; agent path defaults to no auto `LIMIT` (`AI_DB_QUERY_INJECT_LIMIT=false`).
- Paste ERD: `POST /api/db/erd/build?specId=` with `{ schema, format }`; validate via `erd-paste-schema.ts` before Liam CLI.
- Legacy connection ERD builds use schema snapshots only — not live DB introspection at diagram time.
- ERD asset routes: hex `cacheKey` + allowlisted extensions (`erd-security.ts`); connection routes also require UUID `connectionId`.
- Do not expose decrypted DB passwords in API responses or logs.
